              "question": "What is the correct way to say 'she is running'?",
              "options": ["Aringo", "Oringo", "Giringo", "Uringo"],
              "correct_answer": 2,
              "explanation": "'O' is the pronoun suffix for he/she. You add it to the beginning of the verb to give the present tense.."
            },
            {
              "type": "multiple_choice",
              "question": "What does 'amosou' mean?",
              "options": ["I greet her", "She greets me", "I greet you", "We greet you"],
              "correct_answer": 3,
              "explanation": "To show the object of the verb, you add the pronoun suffix to the end of the verb. Thus 'amoso-u' means 'I greet you (plural)'. This word is a bit of an exception since we don't drop the 'o' at the end of the verb before adding the 'u'."
            },
            {
              "type": "multiple_choice",
